.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
Records a heartbeat for the lifecycle action associated with the specified token or instance. This extends the timeout by the length of time defined using the  PutLifecycleHook API call.
.sp
This step is a part of the procedure for adding a lifecycle hook to an Auto Scaling group:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
(Optional) Create a Lambda function and a rule that allows CloudWatch Events to invoke your Lambda function when Amazon EC2 Auto Scaling launches or terminates instances.
.IP \(bu 2
(Optional) Create a notification target and an IAM role. The target can be either an Amazon SQS queue or an Amazon SNS topic. The role allows Amazon EC2 Auto Scaling to publish lifecycle notifications to the target.
.IP \(bu 2
Create the lifecycle hook. Specify whether the hook is used when the instances launch or terminate.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBIf you need more time, record the lifecycle action heartbeat to keep the instance in a pending state.\fP
.IP \(bu 2
If you finish before the timeout period ends, complete the lifecycle action.
.UNINDENT
.sp
For more information, see \fI\%Amazon EC2 Auto Scaling lifecycle hooks\fP in the \fIAmazon EC2 Auto Scaling User Guide\fP .
.sp
See also: AWS API Documentation
.sp
See \(aqaws help\(aq for descriptions of global parameters.
